# ColorHost
A PowerShell module to write customized output to a host.

## Usage
The module can be used in two different ways

### As a regular cmdlet

```powershell
Write-ColorHost
    [[-Objects] <Object[]>]
    [-NoNewLine]
    [-Separator <Object>]
    [-ForegroundColor { ConsoleColor | string }]
    [-BackgroundColor { ConsoleColor | string }]
    [<\CommonParameters\>]
```

### As part of the pipeline

```powershell
Object | Write-ColorHost
           [-NoNewLine]
           [-Separator <Object>]
           [-ForegroundColor { ConsoleColor | string }]
           [-BackgroundColor { ConsoleColor | string }]
           [<\CommonParameters\>]
```

